'''Darkest Knight''' was a title given by the [[Shadow Academy]] in [[22 ABY/Legends|22 ABY]] to their top [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] trainees.

==History==
The title of Darkest Knight was gained following a life-or-death tournament which saw one participant kill the other, evidence of the "survival of the fittest" policy in use by the Academy. The Shadow Academy had been recruiting youths (mainly [[Human/Legends|Humans]]) from the dregs of galactic society, most notably the [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]-based street gang [[Lost Ones]]. Those found to be [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] were trained as Dark Jedi while those who weren't became [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] and [[TIE pilot]]s.

Notable bearers included [[Zekk]] who obtained the title after a life-or-death duel in zero gravity with another student, [[Vilas]], mistaking him for an illusion.

